thread.title: PrepXtra high school football rankings for Week 7
thread.title_full: PrepXtra high school football rankings for Week 7 - PrepXtra Story

author: knoxnews.com
title: PrepXtra high school football rankings for Week 7
text:
1. Maryville (7-0)
This Week: beat Dobyns-Bennett 49-10; Next Week: Idle
Skinny: Rebels, who beat Bearden 41-0 in Week 6, have won 37 consecutive games.
2. Alcoa (5-1)
Last Week: beat Heritage 52-20; This Week: vs. McMinn Central
Skinny: Tornadoes debut at No. 1 in Class 3A state rankings.
3. Fulton (5-1)
Last Week: beat Gibbs 46-0; This Week: vs. Carter
Skinny: No school played Fulton tougher last season than Carter, which fell 18-12.
4. CAK (6-0)
Last Week: beat Donelson Christian 48-13; This Week: vs. Loudon
Skinny: Junior quarterback Cole Smith has completed 76 percent of his passes for 1,581 yards, 17 TDs and two interceptions.
5. Morristown West (5-1)
Last Week: beat Central 24-7; This Week: vs. Morristown East
Skinny: Trojans have won 16 of past 19 against cross-town rival.
6. Farragut (5-0)
Last Week: Idle; This Week: vs. Campbell County
Skinny: Admirals are 13-0 all-time against Campbell County, but last played Cougars in 2004.
7. Oak Ridge (5-1)
Last Week: beat Sevier County 44-34; This Week: vs. Morristown West
Skinny: After starting season slow on offense, Wildcats averaging 47 points in last three games.
8. Greeneville (4-1)
Last Week: idle; This Week: at Sullivan East
Skinny: Greene Devils, who havenâ€™t lost a region game since 2007, have outscored opponents 162-51 this season.
9. Central (4-1)
Last Week: lost to Morristown West 24-7; This Week: at Union County
Skinny: Bobcats trying to get offense on track after five turnovers led to Week 6 loss.
10. Sevier County (4-2)
Last Week: lost to Oak Ridge 44-34; This Week: at Daniel Boone
Skinny: Smoky Bears, who have lost two region games since 2010, try to regroup against winless Daniel Boone.
Chris Thomas
